properties.Name: Route F East Highland Valley Road
properties.AgencyName: Idaho Department of Fish and Game
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use 4-WD trail that provides access to the Boise Front WMA from Highway 21.

properties.Name: FS #190 Mores Mountain Interpretive Trail
properties.TrailDescription: Pedestrian-Only. This trail takes hikers past expansive views including the Sawtooth Mountains to the east and Oregon's Blue Mountains to the west.

properties.Name: Route E Shaw Mountain Road
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use 4-WD trail that provides a route from East Highland Valley Road to the top of Lucky Peak. Access from East Highland Valley Road and #8 Lucky Peak Trail. Connects to #9 Hornet Loop.

properties.Name: Route E Shaw Mountain Road (Non-Motorized)

properties.AccessFrom: Route F East Highland Valley Road
properties.AccessTo: #8 Lucky Peak Trail, #11 West Highland Valley Trail

properties.Name: #77 Sweet Connie
properties.TrailDescription: Popular with equestrians, this trail connects Shafer Butte Area trails with trails of the lower foothills descending from forested heights to open lowlands with a mix of steep, rolling, and tight technical rocky single track. Access via #120 East Side Trail.

properties.Name: #74 Chukar Butte
properties.TrailDescription: Popular with equestrian users, this trail provides expansive views as it traverses from Hidden Springs to Sweet Connie Trail via old two track road and a mix of flowy and technical single track.

properties.Name: #76 Peggy's
properties.TrailDescription: Popular with equestrians, this trail connects Polecat Gulch Reserve with Sweet Connie Trail via the scenic lower Dry Creek Drainage. Located primarily on private land that is utilized for cattle grazing please travel on system trails only and slow down when encountering cattle.
properties.AccessTo: Chukar Butte Trail, Sweet Connie Trail

properties.Name: #58 Harrison Ridge
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley and Boise Parks and Recreation
properties.TrailDescription: This trail provides an overlook of Harrison Hollow with views of the Foothills to the east.
properties.AccessFrom: Harrison Hollow Trailhead just of N Bogus Basin Rd

properties.Name: #57 Harrison Hollow
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley
properties.TrailDescription: This trail provides an out-and-back all-weather trail opportunity as well as providing access to the heart of the Hillside to Hollow Reserve.
properties.AccessFrom: Harrison Hollow Trailhead just off N Bogus Basin Rd
properties.AccessTo: #52 Kemper's Ridge, #58 Harrison Ridge, Harrison Hollow Loop

properties.Name: Harrison Hollow Loop
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley
properties.TrailDescription: This trail provides a short loop opportunity with #57 Harrison Hollow Trail.
properties.AccessFrom: #52 Kemper's Ridge, #57 Harrison Hollow, Down and Out
properties.AccessTo: #52 Kemper's Ridge, #57 Harrison Hollow, Down and Out

properties.Name: Down and Out
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley
properties.TrailDescription: A short and steep route, managed by the Land Trust of the Treasure Valley, linking #51 Who Now Loop to #57 Harrison Hollow Trail.
properties.AccessFrom: #51 Who Now Loop, #52 Kemper's Ridge, #57 Harrison Hollow
properties.AccessTo: #51 Who Now Loop, #52 Kemper's Ridge, #57 Harrison Hollow

properties.Name: #52 Kemper's Ridge
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley and Boise Parks and Recreation
properties.TrailDescription: With steep ups and downs this trail spans the highest ridge and crosses the highest points in the Hillside to Hollow Reserve, providing great views of the Foothills and Boise's North End.

properties.Name: #51 Who Now Loop
properties.TrailDescription: This true loop trail intersects several other trails in Hillside to Hollow Reserve providing users short and long loop options.
properties.AccessTo: #50 Hippie Shake, #52 Kemper's Ridge, #53 Buena Vista

properties.Name: #50 Hippie Shake
properties.TrailDescription: This trail provides short loop opportunities from Harrison Hollow when combined with Who Now Loop and Kemper's Ridge

properties.Name: #53 Buena Vista
properties.TrailDescription: Climbing from Hill Road to the highest ridge in the Hillside to Hollow Reserve, this trail provides access to the heart of the reserve and a variety of views, from the tree tops of the city to ridgeline overlooks.

properties.Name: #54 Robert Smylie
properties.TrailDescription: This trail provides loop opportunities with #53 Buena Vista Trail and #55 West Climb Trail. Enjoy the treetop views of north Boise.

properties.Name: #56 Full Sail
properties.TrailDescription: This trail provides access to the Hillside to Hollow Reserve from Hillside Park. Take in the treetop views of north Boise as you climb above Hillside Junior High and traverse to #53 Buena Vista Trail and #55 West Climb Trail.

properties.Name: #55 West Climb
properties.TrailDescription: This trail provides quick access to the Hillside to Hollow Reserve from Ussery Street.
properties.AccessFrom: N Ussery St Parking Area off W Hill Rd
properties.AccessTo: #53 Buena Vista, #54 Robert Smylie, #56 Full Sail

properties.Name: #78 Dry Creek
properties.AgencyName: Boise Parks and Recreation, USFS, BLM
properties.TrailDescription: Connecting lower Bogus Basin Road and the Boise Ridge Road this trail ascends one of the largest drainages in the Boise Foothills winding its way through desert riparian habitat to pine and fir covered slopes.
properties.AccessTo: #77 Sweet Connie, #79 Shingle Creek, #80 Sheep Camp

properties.Name: #80 Sheep Camp
properties.TrailDescription: This trail connects #33 Hard Guy Trail to #78 Dry Creek Trail.

properties.Name: #79 Shingle Creek
properties.TrailDescription: Ascending a major tributary to Dry Creek this trail provides loop opportunities with #78 Dry Creek Trail and #33 Hard Guy Trail, as it climbs through desert riparian habitat up to pine and fir covered slopes.
properties.AccessTo: #53 Buena Vista, #54 Robert Smylie, #56 Full Sail

properties.Name: FS #210 Mahalo (Non-motorized)
properties.TrailDescription: This trail twists and turns through ferns and pines, taking you over rocks, roots, and drops. Because of thick vegetation and tight turns you'll be riding over many of the obstacles before you know it!

properties.Name: LT #6 To Dry Creek
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley
properties.TrailDescription: This former logging road connects the Trails to #78 Dry Creek Trail.

properties.Name: LT #5 Ponderosa Pine Overlook
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley
properties.TrailDescription: This former logging road provides a direct route to the Ponderosa Pine Overlook
properties.AccessFrom: Trailhead just off Bogus Basin Rd

properties.Name: LT #4 Snowshoe Hare Loop
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley
properties.TrailDescription: This former logging road provides a short loop opportunity when combined with Ponderosa Pine Overlook Trail and Doug Fir Loop Trail
properties.AccessTo: Ponderosa Pine Overlook, Doug Fir Loop

properties.Name: LT #3 Doug Fir Loop
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley
properties.TrailDescription: This old logging road is a great choice for longer loop options in the Dry Creek area.
properties.AccessFrom: Ponderosa Pine Overlook, Snowshoe Hare Loop
properties.AccessTo: Ponderosa Pine Overlook, Snowshoe Hare Loop

properties.Name: LT #1 Headwaters Out/Back
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley
properties.TrailDescription: This old logging road winds through the forest below the ridge and ends at the creek. You can turn around to return to the trailhead or take the 1.1-mile Connection over to Doug Fir Loop for a longer outing.
properties.AccessFrom: Shafer Butte Rd just off Bogus Basin Rd, Headwaters Connection Trail
properties.AccessTo: Shafer Butte Rd just off Bogus Basin Rd, Headwaters Connection Trail

properties.Name: LT #2 Headwaters Connection
properties.AgencyName: Land Trust of the Treasure Valley
properties.TrailDescription: This old logging road provides a link between trails accesed from Twelve Mile Trailhead and Ridge Road Trailhead.

properties.Name: FS #210 Mahalo
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-use Motorized section of the Mahalo trail. Access this trail via FS Road 275C.
properties.AccessFrom: Boise Ridge Road, Non-motorized Mahalo Trail Section
properties.AccessTo: Boise Ridge Road, Non-motorized Mahalo Trail Section

properties.Name: #35A Red-Winged Blackbird (Middle)
properties.TrailDescription: Middle segment of Red-Winged Blackbird Trail. This trail provides a Pedestrian-Only Route from The Grove Trailhead to Chickadee Ridge.

properties.Name: #37 Owl's Roost
properties.TrailDescription: Trail runs along a riparian area made up of native and exotic vegetation. Bird watchers may catch a glimpse of roosting owls.

properties.Name: #38 The Grove
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a Pedestrian-Only experience through an area of native and exotic trees providing a nice shade alternate to the hot sagebrush environment of the Foothills.

properties.Name: #28 Crestline
properties.TrailDescription: One of the most heavily used trails in the Ridge to Rivers system. Trail provides a multi-use non-motorized route to less crowded trails in the Foothills.
properties.AccessTo: #23 Military Reserve Connection, #24 Sidewinder, #4 8th St. Motorcycle Trail

properties.Name: #29 Lower Hull's Gulch
properties.TrailDescription: One of the most heavily used trails on the Ridge to Rivers system. Following Hulls Creek, this trail provides moderate technical riding opportunities.
properties.AccessTo: #28 Crestline (via #4 8th Street Motorcycle Trail), #0 Hulls Gulch Interpretive Trail

properties.Name: #34 Hull's Pond
properties.TrailDescription: Provides a short walk for small children and a great opportunity for bird watching.

properties.Name: #35 Gold Finch
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a, multi-use non-motorized, route from #36 Red Fox to The Grove Trailhead. Connects to #37 Owls Roost.

properties.Name: #35A Red-Winged Blackbird
properties.TrailDescription: Provides a Pedestrian-Only route, paralleling and crossing Hulls Creek, to Chickadee Ridge.

properties.Name: #4A Hull's Ridge
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use Motorized connection to the Boise Ridge Road.

properties.Name: #5 Freestone Ridge
properties.TrailDescription: A long rocky ridg trails that drops steeply from #42 Fat Tire Traverse all the way to #26 Three Bears.
properties.AccessFrom: #42 Fat Tire Traverse, #26 Three Bears Trail

properties.Name: #24 Sidewinder
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use Non-Motorized trail. Trail winds along the south side of Hulls Ridge providing great views and fast single track.

properties.Name: #32 Scott's
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use Non-Motorized trail; Provides a route to upper 8th Street from #31 Corrals Trail.

properties.Name: #30 Bob's
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use Non-Motorized Trail. A popular trail for mountain bikers who like a trail that is a little more technical.

properties.Name: #33 Hard Guy
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use Non-Motorized trail. Ride from sagebrush grasslands to broken timber slopes. If you take on this trail, be prepared for a tough climb.

properties.Name: #71 Red Tail
properties.TrailDescription: This trail is the main trail in the Hidden Springs Area. Loops are possible when Red Tail Trail is combined with other Ridge to Rivers trails and area roads.
properties.AccessFrom: Dry Creek Parking Area/Trailhead, N Cartwright Rd

properties.Name: #72 Lookout Loop
properties.TrailDescription: Provides great views of lower Dry Creek and the Hidden Springs community.

properties.Name: #20 Ridge Crest
properties.TrailDescription: This trail links the Cottonwood Creek and Freestone Creek drainages.

properties.Name: #14 Tram

properties.Name: Pedestrian-Only (Table Rock)
properties.TrailDescription: Pedestrian-Only option for the lower segment of #15 Table Rock Trail.

properties.Name: #15 Table Rock
properties.TrailDescription: Hike or ride from the Old Penitentiary to the top of Table Rock.

properties.Name: #15A Old Pen
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides views of the Old Penitentiary and Idaho Botanical Gardens. Use as an alternate to the lower segment of #15 Table Rock Trail.

properties.Name: Connector
properties.TrailDescription: Connects #15 Table Rock to #14 Tram.  Allows access to #16B Rock Island and #16A Rock Garden Trails.

properties.Name: #16A Rock Garden
properties.TrailDescription: Loops off of eastern segment of #16 Table Rock Loop Trail. Allows access to #16B Rock Island Trail.

properties.Name: #17 Table Rock Quarry
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides an upper loop of Table Rock when combined with #15 Table Rock Trail.

properties.Name: #18 Quarry
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides views of historic quarry activity as well as views of Boises East End.

properties.Name: Access Trail (Shoshone-Paiute Tribes Trail)

properties.Name: #39A Kestrel

properties.Name: #0 Hull's Gulch Interpretive Loop

properties.Name: #22 Central Ridge

properties.Name: #22A Central Ridge Spur (North)
properties.TrailDescription: Northern segment of #22A Central Ridge Spur.

properties.Name: #22A Central Ridge Spur (South)
properties.TrailDescription: Southern segment of #22A Central Ridge Spur.
properties.AccessTo: #22 Central Ridge Trail, #22B Freestone Creek Trail

properties.Name: #22C Mountain Cove
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides an alternate to riding or hiking Mountain Cove Rd. Allows access to #23 Military Reserve Connector, #20 Ridge Crest, #26 Three Bears Trail.

properties.Name: #23 Military Reserve Connection
properties.TrailDescription: Trail connects Central Foothills Trails to trails in Military Reserve.

properties.Name: #23A Elephant Rock Loop
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a short loop opportunity with views of downtown Boise.

properties.Name: #25A Eagle Ridge Loop
properties.TrailDescription: Trail loops around Eagle Ridge. Provides great views of downtown Boise and the foothills.

properties.Name: #27A Toll Road Trail
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a route to the interior of Military Reserve.

properties.Name: Connector
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a Pedestrian-Only connection of Eagle Ridge and Cottonwood Creek.
properties.AccessTo: #25 Eagle Ridge Trail, #27 Cottonwood Creek Trail

properties.Name: #2 Five Mile Gulch
properties.TrailDescription: Five Mile Gulch is a large drainage containing mature stands of Cottonwood and Locust trees seldom seen in the foothills.
properties.AccessFrom: Five Mile Creek Trail Access Point

properties.Name: #3 Watchman
properties.TrailDescription: Trail connects lower segment of #2 Five Mile Gulch Trail with the upper end of #26 Three Bears Trail and #6 Femrite's Patrol. Provides excellent views on fun singletrack.
properties.AccessFrom: #2 Five Mile Gulch Trail, #26 Three Bears Trail
properties.AccessTo: #2 Five Mile Gulch Trail, #26 Three Bears Trail, #6 Femrite's Patrol

properties.Name: #7 Orchard Gulch
properties.TrailDescription: Orchard Gulch contains numerous fruit trees reminiscent of an earlier era.

properties.Name: #26 Three Bears
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides link between lower and upper Foothills trails. Access from Mountain Cove Road, Rocky Canyon Road or #26A Shanes Trail.
properties.AccessFrom: Five Mile Creek Trail Access Point

properties.Name: #26A Shane's
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides link between the Military Reserve Trails and trails in the upper Foothills. Combine with #26 Three Bears Trail for a great mid-elevation loop.
properties.AccessTo: #20A Bucktail Trail, #22 Central Ridge Trail, #26A Shane's Trail to Rocky Canyon

properties.Name: #92 Shindig
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a route between #91 Deer Point Trail / #94 Elk Meadows Trail and lower ski area Cat Tracks.
properties.AccessFrom: #91 Deer Point Trail, #94 Elk Meadows Trail, N Bogus Creek Road
properties.AccessTo: #142 Sunshine Trail, #141 Pioneer Trail, #143 Bogus Creek Trail

properties.Name: #93 The Face
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a route across the face of Shafer Butte.

properties.Name: #95 Tempest
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides access to the north face of Shafer Butte. Access from #140 Lodge Trail. Connects to #93 The Face and #149 Packing trails.
properties.AccessTo: #93 The Face Trail, #149 Packing Trail, #144 Cabin Traverse Trail

properties.Name: FS #198 Mores Mountain Bike Trail
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a loop opportunity, around Mores Mountain, when combined with NFD Rd 374.

properties.Name: #102 Rim
properties.TrailDescription: The Rim Trail provides a pedestrian-only experience, overlooking the Boise River valley. Users will discover the historic Kelton Ramp located on the southeast end of the trail. Trail also features numerous interpretive signs and three interpretive overlooks.

properties.Name: #103 Oregon Trail
properties.TrailDescription: Trail parallels historic Oregon Trail through the Oregon Trail Reserve. Ruts from the historic Oregon Trail are visible from the trail.

properties.Name: #141 Pioneer
properties.TrailDescription: Maintained as a ski area cat track.

properties.Name: #142 Sunshine
properties.TrailDescription: Maintained as a ski area cat track.

properties.Name: #143 Bogus Creek
properties.TrailDescription: Maintained as a ski area cat track. Bogus Creek Trail provides a route from the Shindig Trail / Pioneer Trail junction down to Simplot Lodge.

properties.Name: #149 Packing Trail
properties.TrailDescription: Maintained as a ski area cat road. Provides a route up the north face of Shafer Butte.

properties.Name: #122 Sinker Creek
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a loop opportunity off of #120 Eastside Trail. If you go down, be prepared for the climb out.
properties.AccessTo: #124 Mr. Big Trail, #123 DB Connector Trail'

properties.Name: #123 DB Connector
properties.TrailDescription: Trail connects the middle of #120 Eastside Trail to the middle of #122 Sinker Creek Trail. Provides several loop options off of both connecting trails.

properties.Name: Access Trail (#110 Seaman Gulch)
properties.TrailDescription: Provides access to #110 Seaman Gulch Trail from Seaman Gulch Rd.

properties.Name: #110 Seaman Gulch
properties.TrailDescription: Connects to #112 Wild Phlox Trail and #111 Valley View Trail.

properties.Name: #111 Valley View
properties.TrailDescription: Check out the great views of West Boise. Loop off #110 Seaman Gulch Trail

properties.Name: #114 Veterans (Dog On-Leash)
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides route from east entrance of Dry Creek Cemetery to west end of Big Springs Blvd. Please respect the Dry Creek and Idaho Veterans Cemeteries by controlling pets and staying only on designated trails.

properties.Name: #8 Lucky Peak
properties.AgencyName: Idaho Department of Fish and Game
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use 4-WD trail that offers great views of the Treasure Valley and provides a intense workout for those who chose to hike or ride it. Connects other Boise Front WMA trails.
properties.AccessFrom: #12 Homestead Trail, Route E Shaw Mountain Road

properties.Name: #11 West Highland Valley
properties.AgencyName: Idaho Department of Fish and Game
properties.TrailDescription: Route follows an old road bed. While strenuous, it is one of the easier routes into this wildlife area. Connects with #13 Cobb Trail
properties.AccessFrom: West Highland Valley Trail Access Point

properties.Name: #12 Homestead
properties.AgencyName: Idaho Department of Fish and Game
properties.TrailDescription: Two miles and a climb of 1000 feet, this trail takes you into the heart of this wildlife area. This aggressive, multi-use non-motorized, route can be done as an out and back or a link to the other trails that provide a variety of loop opportunities.

properties.Name: #13 Cobb
properties.AgencyName: Idaho Department of Fish and Game
properties.TrailDescription: Often combined with other trails for a loop, the route takes you near old homesteads and springs.

properties.Name: #16B Rock Island (West)
properties.TrailDescription: Western segment of #16B Rock Island Trail. Features moderate to advanced, stone, technical features. Rock Island is a purpose-built trail - as such mountain bikers have the right of way on this trail. Respect this opportunity for technical riding by staying on designated routes.

properties.Name: #6 Femrite's Patrol
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use Motorized trail. Access from #4 (motorized), #5 (non-motorized). Connects to #26 (non-motorized) and #3 (non-motorized).

properties.Name: #31 Corrals
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use Non-motorized trail. Provides a route from Bogus Basin Road to 8th Street.
properties.AccessFrom: 8th Street ATV Trailhead, N Bogus Basin Road

properties.Name: Connector
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use Non-Motorized trail.

properties.Name: #101 Basalt
properties.TrailDescription: Basalt Trail provides loop opportunities for users of the Oregon Trail Reserve and great views of the basalt cliff the reserve is perched on.

properties.Name: #94 Elk Meadows
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a route around the eastside of Shafer Butte.

properties.Name: #140 Lodge
properties.TrailDescription: Maintained as a ski area cat track, Lodge Trail provides access to the north face of Shafer Butte and several connecting trails.

properties.Name: #144 Cabin Traverse
properties.TrailDescription: Maintained as a ski area cat track. Trail provides access to the top of Shafer Butte.

properties.Name: #91 Deer Point
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a moderate route from Simplot Lodge to the #92 and #94 trail junction.

properties.Name: #96 Brewers Byway
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides route from Pioneer Lodge to the top of #92 Shindig Trail. Features rolling single track thru timbered and rocky slopes. Use as easier access to higher elevation trails.

properties.Name: #120 Eastside
properties.TrailDescription: Main trail west of Bogus Basin Rd. Connects with #122 Sinker Creek Trail and #123 DB Connector Trail.

properties.Name: #125 Freddys Stack Rock Trail
properties.TrailDescription: Lollipop shaped loop trail that accesses Stack Rock, providing great views of the Treasure Valley as it meanders across open hillsides, around rock outcroppings and through shady forests.

properties.Name: #126 Big-Stack Cutoff
properties.TrailDescription: Like the name suggests, Big-Stack Cutoff provides a cutoff route between #124 Mr. Big Trail and #125 Freddys Stack Rock Trail.

properties.Name: #124 Mr. Big
properties.TrailDescription: Trail connects the southern end of #120 Eastside Trail to #122 Sinker Creek Trail.

properties.Name: #113 Big Springs Loop
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides loop opportunities when combined with #114 Veterans Trail.

properties.Name: #112 Wild Phlox
properties.TrailDescription: Provides a loop opportunity when combined with #110 Seaman Gulch trail.

properties.Name: #81 Polecat Loop
properties.TrailDescription: Trail features great views of the Treasure Valley and Boise Ridgeline while providing single track around the perimeter of Polecat Gulch.
properties.AccessTo: #83 Quick Draw Trail, #82 Doe Ridge Trail

properties.Name: #83 Quick Draw
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a quick loop option when combined with #81 Polecat Loop and #82 Doe Ridge.

properties.Name: #82 Doe Ridge
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides loop opportunities when combined with #83 Quick Draw Trail or #81 Polecat Loop.

properties.Name: #36A Chickadee Ridge
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides a birds-eye view of Hulls Gulch Reserve.
properties.AccessTo: #36 Red Fox Trail, Connection (#36A Chickadee Ridge), #35A Red-Winged Blackbird Trail (Middle)

properties.Name: Connector
properties.TrailDescription: Trail connects Red Cliffs to Kestrel Trail.

properties.Name: #39 Red Cliffs
properties.TrailDescription: Trail provides great views of Hulls Creek and downtown Boise.
properties.AccessFrom: #29 Lower Hull's Gulch Trail, #28 Crestline Trail
properties.AccessTo: #29 Lower Hull's Gulch Trail, #28 Crestline Trail

properties.Name: #42 Fat Tire Traverse
properties.TrailDescription: This Multi-Use Non-Motorized trail, links #5  (Non-Motorized) to the #4 (Motorized), just east of the Sidewinder junction. The trail allows for great views, while providing an important mid-foothills connection.

properties.Name: #4 8th Street Motorcycle
properties.TrailDescription: Multi-Use Motorized trail that provides access to the Foothills for ATV and motorcycle users. Connects to # 42 (Non-Motorized), #6 (Motorized) and #4A (Motorized).

properties.TrailDescription: Often referred to as The Black Forest,  you will find a pleasant and rewarding trail through cottonwood stands and open sagebrush flats. Please avoid the volunteer trails that meander through the brush as this area is set aside for wildlife to enjoy.

properties.TrailDescription: Trail allows access to #18 Quarry Trail from Eastdale Dr.

properties.Name: #9 Urban Connector
properties.TrailDescription: The Urban Connector Trail provides a short but aerobic loop off of Lower Bobs and Highlands Trails.  It is named for BLM Smokejumper Mark Urban, who was killed during a training jump in 2013.  The trail was improved by BLM smokejumpers, and they maintain the trail in his honor through the Ridge to Rivers Adopt A Trail Program.

properties.Name: #1 Highlands
properties.TrailDescription: Singletrack trail connecting #31 Corrals Trail and lower #30 Bob's Trail.

properties.Name: #98 Around the Mountain
properties.TrailDescription: By combining with Deer Point and either Morningstar or Brewers Byway Trails, the Around the Mountain Trail takes visitors on a 360-degree tour of the Bogus Basin Ski area. Trail contains banked turns, short rock features, and stunning long distance views of the Snake River Plain, Owyhee Mountains, Sawtooth Mountains, Squaw Butte, and the West Mountain area south of McCall. The trail is best ridden in a counter-clockwise direction, beginning on the Deer Point Trail at the Simplot Lodge.

properties.Name: #16B Rock Island (Jump Line)
properties.TrailDescription: The Rock Island Jump Line is a short but thrilling piece of trail.  It contains numerous table top style jumps combined with banked turns, as it bisects the lower Rock Island Loop.  This piece of trail is one-way, downhill only, and mountain bikers have the right of way.
properties.AccessFrom: #16A Rock Garden Trail, #16B Rock Island Trail (west)
properties.AccessTo: #16A Rock Garden Trail, #16B Rock Island Trail (west)

properties.Name: #16B Rock Island (Deer Path)
properties.TrailDescription: Following an old deer path, this leg of Rock Island Trail provides a midway connection with #14 Tram and #16B Rock Island.  Managed as a technical mountain biking opportunity, users are asked to yield to down-hill riders.
properties.AccessFrom: Table Rock Summit Parking lot, #14 Tram Trail
